es/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/coinflip.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/platform.json`\n\n---\n\n### 4. .so Files in target/ (Complete List)\n\nFound 92 .so files across debug, release, and sbpf targets. **Actively deployed binaries**:\n\n```\nsolana/target/deploy/\n├── coinflip.so (331,256 bytes) — Main program binary\n└── platform.so (215,464 bytes)  — Main program binary\n\nsolana/target/sbpf-solana-solana/release/deps/\n├── solana_program-072e2a1ef7618bd5.so\n├── solana_zk_sdk-25eb3f1a039bc1c1.so\n├── spl_discriminator-c07b80c972b66114.so\n├── spl_program_error-e3176d0118503053.so\n├── spl_pod-cb99b031206112dc.so\n├── spl_type_length_value-10e1b514f6e4e51c.so\n├── spl_token_group_interface-590398a192a381f5.so\n├── spl_memo-1c3bad1b551f9b4f.so\n├── spl_tlv_account_resolution-71ac12ac8a4d56f1.so\n├── spl_elgamal_registry-4307178ba6db05fb.so\n├── spl_transfer_hook_interface-209fa8feb53442a1.so\n... (78 more macro/build-related .so files in debug targets)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Test Scripts and Bootstrap Utilities\n\n**Available Scripts** in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/scripts/`:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **deploy-devnet.sh** | Bash script: build + deploy to devnet; validates SBF toolchain v1.52+; checks wallet balance; runs init-devnet-config.ts after deploy |\n| **init-devnet-config.ts** | TypeScript: idempotent config initialization (skips if already created); loads wallet from `~/.config/solana/id.json`; calls `initializePlatform()` + `initializeConfig()` on both programs |\n| **join-devnet-match.ts** | TypeScript: helper to join a match on devnet |\n| **test-devnet-lifecycle.ts** | TypeScript: full integration test lifecycle on devnet |\n\n**Test Files** in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/`:\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| **coinflip.ts** | 33,120 | Main bankrun tests: init, create match, join, resolve (heads/tails), payout settlement |\n| **platform.ts** | 7,320 | Platform program bankrun tests: initialize, player profiles, fee tracking |\n| **devnet-integration.md** | 2,077 | Documentation (not executable) |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Workspace Structure\n\n**Cargo Workspace** (`solana/Cargo.toml`):\n```toml\n[workspace]\nmembers = [\n    \"shared\",              # Shared lib (not deployed, pure types/helpers)\n    \"programs/coinflip\",   # Coinflip program\n    \"programs/platform\",   # Platform program\n]\n\n[workspace.dependencies]\nanchor-lang = \"0.32.1\"\norao-solana-vrf = { version = \"0.7.0\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\nrng-shared = { path = \"shared\" }\nsolana-sha256-hasher = \"2.3\"\n```\n\n**Program Dependencies**:\n\n| Program | Deps |\n|---------|------|\n| **coinflip** | anchor-lang, rng-shared, platform (w/ cpi feature), orao-solana-vrf |\n| **platform** | anchor-lang, rng-shared, orao-solana-vrf |\n| **shared** | anchor-lang, orao-solana-vrf, solana-sha256-hasher |\n\n**Build Features**:\n- `mock-vrf` (default) — uses mock VRF for local testing\n- `no-default-features` — disables mock-vrf, uses real Orao VRF (for devnet deploy)\n- `cpi` — enables CPI interface (coinflip only, for platform CPI calls)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Test Setup Patterns\n\n**Bankrun (No Live Validator)**:\n```typescript\nconst context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n  { address: opponent.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData(100 * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL) },\n  { address: mockOraoProgram.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // ... more accounts\n]);\n\nconst provider = new BankrunProvider(context);\nconst program = new Program<Coinflip>(IDL, provider);\n```\n\n**Devnet Integration** (real validator):\n```typescript\nconst connection = new Connection(\"https://api.devnet.solana.com\", \"confirmed\");\nconst wallet = new Wallet(keypair);\nconst provider = new AnchorProvider(connection, wallet, { commitment: \"confirmed\" });\nconst program = new Program(idl, provider);\n```\n\n**Package Scripts**:\n```json\n{\n  \"test\": \"anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe Solana workspace is a standard Anchor 0.32.1 setup with:\n- **2 deployed programs** (coinflip, platform) + **1 shared lib** (rng-shared)\n- **Comprehensive tests** using bankrun (no validator) with mock VRF for fast iteration\n- **Devnet integration scripts** with real Orao VRF, idempotent config initialization\n- **Feature gating** (`mock-vrf` default, `no-default-features` for devnet) to flip between test/production\n- **PDA-based accounts** with deterministic seeds for matches, configs, and player profiles\n- **IDL-driven tests** that load generated IDLs from `target/idl/` to stay in sync with program code\n\nAll keypairs are generated on-the-fly in tests; the only persistent keypairs are the program deploy keypairs in `target/deploy/`."}],"totalDurationMs":63145,"totalTokens":53997,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":821,"cache_read_input_tokens":50046,"output_tokens":3123,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":821,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011paUumEGR8dxw4u7sjMLhC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Playwright Configuration & E2E Test Structure Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Playwright configuration and E2E test structure in the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Playwright Configuration Files\n\n**Located at**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`\n\n#### `playwright.config.ts` (Default / Visual Regression Suite)\n- **Test Directory**: `./e2e`\n- **Port**: `http://localhost:3000`\n- **Mode**: Mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\"`)\n- **Browser**: Single worker (workers: 1), Chromium only\n- **Viewport**: 1280×1080\n- **Features**:\n  - Screenshot snapshots for visual regression (max diff ratio: 1.5%)\n  - Network idle wait strategy\n  - Reuses existing dev server in non-CI environments\n  - Screenshot disabled by default (off)\n  - Fully parallel test execution\n\n#### `playwright.real.config.ts` (Real Wallet Mode / Devnet Suite)\n- **Test Directory**: `./e2e` (same, filtered by pattern)\n- **Port**: `http://localhost:3001`\n- **Mode**: Real mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"`)\n- **Test Match**: `real/**/*.spec.ts` (only tests in the `real/` subdirectory)\n- **RPC URL**: `https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n- **Browser**: Chromium only\n- **Purpose**: Tests against real wallet mode without browser extension\n\n---\n\n### 2. E2E Test Directory Structure\n\n```\napps/platform/e2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                     # Shared test utilities & fixtures\n├── visual/                         # Visual regression tests\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts             # Route baseline snapshots\n│   └── states.spec.ts             # State variant snapshots\n├── real/                          # Real wallet mode tests\n│   └── startup.spec.ts            # Smoke test for devnet startup\n└── __snapshots__/                 # Baseline PNG files\n    └── visual/\n        ├── routes.spec.ts/        # 12 route baselines (404, home, coinflip, crash, etc.)\n        └── states.spec.ts/        # 6 state variant baselines\n```\n\n**Total test code**: 413 lines across 4 files\n\n---\n\n### 3. Shared Fixtures: `e2e/fixtures.ts` (110 lines)\n\n**Export**: Custom `test` fixture extending Playwright's base test\n\n**Features**:\n- **Deterministic PRNG**: Mulberry32 seeded PRNG (seed: 42) replaces `Math.random()`\n- **Deterministic Crypto**: Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for keypair generation\n- **Frozen Time**: Freezes `Date.now()` to `2026-01-01T00:00:00Z` (1767225600000 ms)\n- **Animation Freezing**: Injects CSS to disable all CSS animations/transitions and pauses SVG SMIL animations\n- **Console Error Collection**: Captures console errors and fails test if any found\n- **Auto-Wait**: Wraps `page.goto()` to:\n  - Wait for `networkidle`\n  - Inject freeze CSS after navigation\n  - Wait for `document.fonts.ready`\n  - Settle time (300ms)\n\n**Usage Pattern**: \n```typescript\nimport { test, expect } from \"../fixtures\";\ntest(\"example\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"name.png\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Visual Regression Tests\n\n#### `visual/routes.spec.ts` (63 lines)\nTests baseline snapshots of all major routes:\n- Home (`/`)\n- Coinflip (`/coinflip`)\n- Lord of RNGs (`/lord-of-rngs`)\n- Close Call (`/close-call`)\n- Crash (`/crash`)\n- Game of Trades (`/game-of-trades`)\n- Profile (`/profile`)\n- Quests (`/quests`)\n- Loot (`/loot`)\n- Fairness (`/fairness`)\n- Leaderboard (`/leaderboard`)\n- 404 (`/nonexistent`)\n\n**Snapshot Location**: `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/*.png`\n\n#### `visual/states.spec.ts` (168 lines)\nTests state variants with wallet connection/disconnection:\n\n**Home Page Tests**:\n- Wallet disconnected baseline\n- Wallet connected (triggers `.rpg-wallet-icon` click, waits for `.rpg-wallet-icon--connected` class)\n\n**Profile Page Tests**:\n- Wallet connected variant\n\n**Coinflip Page Tests**:\n- Wallet disconnected baseline\n- Wallet connected variant\n- Error toast position (injects `.coinflip-error-toast` element with error message)\n\n**Key Pattern**: Tests clear localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`), perform actions, re-inject animation freeze CSS, wait 300ms, then snapshot.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Real Wallet Mode (Devnet) Tests\n\n#### `real/startup.spec.ts` (72 lines)\n\n**Fixture**: Custom `realPage` fixture (no determinism, no frozen time)\n**Suite**: \"Real mode startup\"\n\n**Tests**:\n1. **App Loads Without Errors**:\n   - Navigates to `/` with `networkidle` wait\n   - Verifies wallet icon is visible\n   - Checks wallet icon does NOT have `--connected` class\n   - Verifies amount shows em dash \"—\" (disconnected balance)\n\n2. **Wallet Click Doesn't Crash**:\n   - Navigates to home\n   - Clicks `.rpg-wallet-icon`\n   - Waits 1 second\n   - Verifies wallet icon still visible\n   - Verifies main title (`.rpg-title`) still visible\n\n**Purpose**: Smoke test that real mode startup works without console errors.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Package.json Test Scripts\n\n#### `apps/platform/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n    \"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\",\n    \"test:real\": \"playwright test --config playwright.real.config.ts\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### `sources/rng-utopia/package.json` (Root)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"turbo run test\",\n    \"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual\",\n    \"test:programs\": \"cd solana && anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Note**: Full root `test` script runs turbo, which cascades to all workspaces. Currently no `test:e2e` or `test:e2e:devnet` commands exist yet (per spec 203 requirements).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Related Configurations\n\n**Vitest Config** (wallet package only):\n- Only `packages/wallet/vitest.config.ts` exists\n- Uses jsdom environment with globals\n- **Platform app** does NOT have vitest config (uses Playwright for testing)\n\n**Vite Config** (`apps/platform/vite.config.ts`):\n- React plugin + Node polyfills (buffer, crypto, stream, util)\n- Dev server on port 3000\n- Alias: `@` → `./src`\n- Manual chunk splitting for vendor libraries\n\n**TypeScript Config** (`apps/platform/tsconfig.json`):\n- Extends `@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.react.json`\n- Includes Vite client types\n- Path alias: `@/*` → `./src/*`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Outstanding Work (Per Spec 203)\n\nThe spec defines additional E2E suites that **do not yet exist**:\n\n**Missing**:\n- [ ] Local deterministic suite (`pnpm test:e2e`) with `solana-test-validator`\n- [ ] Local bootstrap/teardown scripts\n- [ ] Dual-browser-context fixture for two-player flows\n- [ ] Full coinflip lifecycle tests (create → join → resolve → claim)\n- [ ] On-chain state assertions (match PDA, treasury fees, player profiles)\n- [ ] Cancel flow tests\n- [ ] Error scenario tests\n- [ ] Devnet tests using real VRF fulfillment\n- [ ] Helper utilities for E2E (selectors, page objects, chain interactions)\n\n**Current Coverage**:\n- ✅ Visual regression baseline tests (12 routes + 6 state variants)\n- ✅ Real wallet mode smoke test (basic connectivity)\n- ✅ Deterministic fixture infrastructure (PRNG, time freezing, animation disabling)\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Files Summary\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | 45 | Visual regression config (mock mode) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | 42 | Real wallet devnet config |\n| `e2e/fixtures.ts` | 110 | Shared deterministic test utilities |\n| `e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts` | 63 | Route baseline snapshots |\n| `e2e/visual/states.spec.ts` | 168 | State variant snapshots |\n| `e2e/real/startup.spec.ts` | 72 | Real mode smoke test |\n| **Total** | **413** | **Existing test code** |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Architecture Insights\n\n**Two-Suite Pattern**:\n1. **Visual Regression Suite**: Uses mock mode with frozen randomness/time for pixel-perfect baselines\n2. **Real Wallet Mode Suite**: Minimal smoke test; no determinism needed, just validates startup\n\n**Determinism Strategy**:\n- Seeded PRNG for reproducible wallet state\n- Frozen clock to eliminate timestamp-based variability\n- Disabled animations to prevent timing-dependent visual differences\n- Console error collection as test failure signal\n\n**Testing Entry Points**:\n- `pnpm test:visual` — runs visual regression suite\n- `pnpm test:visual:update` — updates snapshot baselines\n- `pnpm test:real` — runs real wallet mode tests\n\n**Snapshot Storage**:\n- PNG snapshots stored in `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/` and `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/states.spec.ts/`\n- One snapshot per test case (e.g., `home.png`, `coinflip-connected.png`)\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete Playwright and E2E infrastructure as it exists today. The spec 203 checklist shows that significant work remains to implement full lifecycle integration tests with on-chain validation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a905490f96ec75e77 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51619\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 90519</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6036e3a-bc98-4f9f-8839-caeed7dcba03","uuid":"954fa495-2d37-4004-9b4a-a1c25d91be23","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the existing Playwright configuration and E2E test structure in the codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. Find all Playwright config files (playwright*.config.ts or similar)\n2. Find all existing E2E test files and their directory structure\n3. Look at the existing playwright.real.config.ts file content\n4. Check if there's an e2e/ directory already and what's in it\n5. Look at apps/platform/package.json for existing test scripts\n6. Check the root sources/rng-utopia/package.json for test scripts\n\nSearch thoroughly in /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/\n\nProvide the full content of key files found.","agentId":"a905490f96ec75e77","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Playwright Configuration & E2E Test Structure Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Playwright configuration and E2E test structure in the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Playwright Configuration Files\n\n**Located at**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`\n\n#### `playwright.config.ts` (Default / Visual Regression Suite)\n- **Test Directory**: `./e2e`\n- **Port**: `http://localhost:3000`\n- **Mode**: Mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\"`)\n- **Browser**: Single worker (workers: 1), Chromium only\n- **Viewport**: 1280×1080\n- **Features**:\n  - Screenshot snapshots for visual regression (max diff ratio: 1.5%)\n  - Network idle wait strategy\n  - Reuses existing dev server in non-CI environments\n  - Screenshot disabled by default (off)\n  - Fully parallel test execution\n\n#### `playwright.real.config.ts` (Real Wallet Mode / Devnet Suite)\n- **Test Directory**: `./e2e` (same, filtered by pattern)\n- **Port**: `http://localhost:3001`\n- **Mode**: Real mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"`)\n- **Test Match**: `real/**/*.spec.ts` (only tests in the `real/` subdirectory)\n- **RPC URL**: `https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n- **Browser**: Chromium only\n- **Purpose**: Tests against real wallet mode without browser extension\n\n---\n\n### 2. E2E Test Directory Structure\n\n```\napps/platform/e2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                     # Shared test utilities & fixtures\n├── visual/                         # Visual regression tests\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts             # Route baseline snapshots\n│   └── states.spec.ts             # State variant snapshots\n├── real/                          # Real wallet mode tests\n│   └── startup.spec.ts            # Smoke test for devnet startup\n└── __snapshots__/                 # Baseline PNG files\n    └── visual/\n        ├── routes.spec.ts/        # 12 route baselines (404, home, coinflip, crash, etc.)\n        └── states.spec.ts/        # 6 state variant baselines\n```\n\n**Total test code**: 413 lines across 4 files\n\n---\n\n### 3. Shared Fixtures: `e2e/fixtures.ts` (110 lines)\n\n**Export**: Custom `test` fixture extending Playwright's base test\n\n**Features**:\n- **Deterministic PRNG**: Mulberry32 seeded PRNG (seed: 42) replaces `Math.random()`\n- **Deterministic Crypto**: Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for keypair generation\n- **Frozen Time**: Freezes `Date.now()` to `2026-01-01T00:00:00Z` (1767225600000 ms)\n- **Animation Freezing**: Injects CSS to disable all CSS animations/transitions and pauses SVG SMIL animations\n- **Console Error Collection**: Captures console errors and fails test if any found\n- **Auto-Wait**: Wraps `page.goto()` to:\n  - Wait for `networkidle`\n  - Inject freeze CSS after navigation\n  - Wait for `document.fonts.ready`\n  - Settle time (300ms)\n\n**Usage Pattern**: \n```typescript\nimport { test, expect } from \"../fixtures\";\ntest(\"example\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"name.png\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Visual Regression Tests\n\n#### `visual/routes.spec.ts` (63 lines)\nTests baseline snapshots of all major routes:\n- Home (`/`)\n- Coinflip (`/coinflip`)\n- Lord of RNGs (`/lord-of-rngs`)\n- Close Call (`/close-call`)\n- Crash (`/crash`)\n- Game of Trades (`/game-of-trades`)\n- Profile (`/profile`)\n- Quests (`/quests`)\n- Loot (`/loot`)\n- Fairness (`/fairness`)\n- Leaderboard (`/leaderboard`)\n- 404 (`/nonexistent`)\n\n**Snapshot Location**: `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/*.png`\n\n#### `visual/states.spec.ts` (168 lines)\nTests state variants with wallet connection/disconnection:\n\n**Home Page Tests**:\n- Wallet disconnected baseline\n- Wallet connected (triggers `.rpg-wallet-icon` click, waits for `.rpg-wallet-icon--connected` class)\n\n**Profile Page Tests**:\n- Wallet connected variant\n\n**Coinflip Page Tests**:\n- Wallet disconnected baseline\n- Wallet connected variant\n- Error toast position (injects `.coinflip-error-toast` element with error message)\n\n**Key Pattern**: Tests clear localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`), perform actions, re-inject animation freeze CSS, wait 300ms, then snapshot.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Real Wallet Mode (Devnet) Tests\n\n#### `real/startup.spec.ts` (72 lines)\n\n**Fixture**: Custom `realPage` fixture (no determinism, no frozen time)\n**Suite**: \"Real mode startup\"\n\n**Tests**:\n1. **App Loads Without Errors**:\n   - Navigates to `/` with `networkidle` wait\n   - Verifies wallet icon is visible\n   - Checks wallet icon does NOT have `--connected` class\n   - Verifies amount shows em dash \"—\" (disconnected balance)\n\n2. **Wallet Click Doesn't Crash**:\n   - Navigates to home\n   - Clicks `.rpg-wallet-icon`\n   - Waits 1 second\n   - Verifies wallet icon still visible\n   - Verifies main title (`.rpg-title`) still visible\n\n**Purpose**: Smoke test that real mode startup works without console errors.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Package.json Test Scripts\n\n#### `apps/platform/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n    \"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\",\n    \"test:real\": \"playwright test --config playwright.real.config.ts\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### `sources/rng-utopia/package.json` (Root)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"turbo run test\",\n    \"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual\",\n    \"test:programs\": \"cd solana && anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Note**: Full root `test` script runs turbo, which cascades to all workspaces. Currently no `test:e2e` or `test:e2e:devnet` commands exist yet (per spec 203 requirements).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Related Configurations\n\n**Vitest Config** (wallet package only):\n- Only `packages/wallet/vitest.config.ts` exists\n- Uses jsdom environment with globals\n- **Platform app** does NOT have vitest config (uses Playwright for testing)\n\n**Vite Config** (`apps/platform/vite.config.ts`):\n- React plugin + Node polyfills (buffer, crypto, stream, util)\n- Dev server on port 3000\n- Alias: `@` → `./src`\n- Manual chunk splitting for vendor libraries\n\n**TypeScript Config** (`apps/platform/tsconfig.json`):\n- Extends `@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.react.json`\n- Includes Vite client types\n- Path alias: `@/*` → `./src/*`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Outstanding Work (Per Spec 203)\n\nThe spec defines additional E2E suites that **do not yet exist**:\n\n**Missing**:\n- [ ] Local deterministic suite (`pnpm test:e2e`) with `solana-test-validator`\n- [ ] Local bootstrap/teardown scripts\n- [ ] Dual-browser-context fixture for two-player flows\n- [ ] Full coinflip lifecycle tests (create → join → resolve → claim)\n- [ ] On-chain state assertions (match PDA, treasury fees, player profiles)\n- [ ] Cancel flow tests\n- [ ] Error scenario tests\n- [ ] Devnet tests using real VRF fulfillment\n- [ ] Helper utilities for E2E (selectors, page objects, chain interactions)\n\n**Current Coverage**:\n- ✅ Visual regression baseline tests (12 routes + 6 state variants)\n- ✅ Real wallet mode smoke test (basic connectivity)\n- ✅ Deterministic fixture infrastructure (PRNG, time freezing, animation disabling)\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Files Summary\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | 45 | Visual regression config (mock mode) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | 42 | Real wallet devnet config |\n| `e2e/fixtures.ts` | 110 | Shared deterministic test utilities |\n| `e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts` | 63 | Route baseline snapshots |\n| `e2e/visual/states.spec.ts` | 168 | State variant snapshots |\n| `e2e/real/startup.spec.ts` | 72 | Real mode smoke test |\n| **Total** | **413** | **Existing test code** |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Architecture Insights\n\n**Two-Suite Pattern**:\n1. **Visual Regression Suite**: Uses mock mode with frozen randomness/time for pixel-perfect baselines\n2. **Real Wallet Mode Suite**: Minimal smoke test; no determinism needed, just validates startup\n\n**Determinism Strategy**:\n- Seeded PRNG for reproducible wallet state\n- Frozen clock to eliminate timestamp-based variability\n- Disabled animations to prevent timing-dependent visual differences\n- Console error collection as test failure signal\n\n**Testing Entry Points**:\n- `pnpm test:visual` — runs visual regression suite\n- `pnpm test:visual:update` — updates snapshot baselines\n- `pnpm test:real` — runs real wallet mode tests\n\n**Snapshot Storage**:\n- PNG snapshots stored in `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/` and `e2e/__snapshots__/visual/states.spec.ts/`\n- One snapshot per test case (e.g., `home.png`, `coinflip-connected.png`)\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete Playwright and E2E infrastructure as it exists today. The spec 203 checklist shows that significant work remains to implement full lifecycle integration tests with on-chain validation."}],"totalDurationMs":90519,"totalTokens":51619,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":645,"cache_read_input_tokens":48318,"output_tokens":2649,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":645,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YMw6MqDidTq39wsiBPVT5b","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Comprehensive Code Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the TestWalletProvider and chain integration code in the RNG Utopia codebase. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. TestWalletProvider (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx`)\n\n**Purpose**: E2E testing wallet that signs real transactions with an injected Keypair against local test-validator.\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Uses real Solana keypair signing (no browser extension needed)\n- Default RPC: `http://127.0.0.1:8899` (localhost)\n- Auto-connects on mount by default\n- Implements full `WalletContextValue` interface\n- `sendAndConfirmTransaction()` for real on-chain interaction\n\n**Constructor Props**:\n```typescript\n{\n  keypair: Keypair                    // Real keypair for signing\n  rpcUrl?: string                     // Default: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\n  autoConnect?: boolean               // Default: true\n}\n```\n\n**Methods**:\n- `connect()` - Verifies keypair by checking account balance\n- `disconnect()` - Clears connection state\n- `sendTransaction(tx)` - Signs and confirms transaction with keypair\n- `signMessage(msg)` - Returns deterministic 64-byte signature from keypair's secret key\n\n---\n\n## 2. Chain Transaction Builders (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n\n**Program ID Configuration**:\n```typescript\n// COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID - reads from env or falls back to IDL\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n// IDL address: \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\n\n// ORAO VRF program (hardcoded)\nconst ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\");\n\n// PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID (for CPI to player_profile)\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n);\n```\n\n**PDA Derivation Functions**:\n- `getMatchPda(creator)` - Derives match account PDA from creator\n- `getConfigPda()` - Derives coinflip config PDA\n- `getOraoNetworkStatePda()` - Derives Orao VRF network state\n- `getOraoRandomnessPda(seed)` - Derives Orao randomness request account\n\n**On-Chain Account Types**:\n- `OnChainMatch` interface defines the match struct with fields like phase (enum variant), tier, result, etc.\n- `RoundPhaseVariant` type: `{ waiting | active | locked | resolving | settled | refunded }`\n\n**Converter Functions**:\n- `tierFromIndex()` - Maps index 0-5 to \"iron\", \"bronze\", \"silver\", \"gold\", \"platinum\", \"diamond\"\n- `sideFromIndex()` - Maps 0→\"heads\", 1→\"tails\"\n- `phaseToUI()` - Converts on-chain phase enum to UI phase (\"created\", \"ready\", \"complete\")\n- `onChainMatchToUI()` - Transforms on-chain match account to `UIMatch` type\n\n**Transaction Builders** (all async):\n1. **`buildCreateMatchTx(connection, creator, tier, side)`**\n   - Creates new match with creator and tier\n   - Derives matchPda and configPda\n   - Returns tx + matchPda\n\n2. **`buildJoinMatchTx(connection, opponent, matchCreator)`**\n   - Joins existing match\n   - Fetches Orao treasury from network state\n   - Derives randomness PDA for VRF request\n   - Accounts: opponent, match, config, Orao accounts, system\n\n3. **`buildCancelMatchTx(connection, creator)`**\n   - Cancels unclaimed match (refunds creator)\n   - Only callable before opponent joins\n\n4. **`buildTimeoutCancelTx(connection, caller, matchCreator, opponent)`**\n   - Force-closes locked match if VRF didn't resolve in time\n   - Any player can call after deadline\n\n5. **`buildClaimPayoutTx(connection, caller, matchCreator, opponent)`**\n   - Settlement instruction: resolves VRF randomness, derives winner, sends payout\n   - CPIs to Platform program to update player profiles\n   - Derives both players' profile PDAs\n\n**Query Functions**:\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()` - Filters for \"waiting\" phase matches\n- `fetchClaimableMatches(pubkey)` - Uses memcmp filters for efficient on-chain filtering by creator/opponent + claimed==false\n- `fetchMatchByCreator(creator)` - Fetches single match by creator\n- `fetchMatch(matchPda)` - Fetches match by address\n- All query functions detect VRF fulfillment and upgrade phase \"locked\" → \"complete\" when randomness arrives\n\n---\n\n## 3. CoinflipContext (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\n**State**:\n```typescript\nactiveMatch: UIMatch | null              // Currently-viewing match\nopenMatches: UIMatch[]                  // All available matches from lobby\nclaimableMatches: UIMatch[]            // Matches user is in (as creator or opponent)\nselectedTier: Tier | null              // Selection for new match\nselectedSide: CoinSide | null          // Selection for new match\nloading: boolean                       // Initial load state\ncreating: boolean                      // Create tx in-flight\njoining: boolean                       // Join tx in-flight\nclaiming: boolean                      // Claim payout tx in-flight\njoiningMatchId: string | null          // Which match user is joining\nerror: string | null                   // Last error message\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- **Smart polling**: 5s interval when VRF pending (\"ready\" phase), 30s when in lobby\n- **VRF animation**: Intercepts ready→complete transition to show 3s flip animation before settling\n- **Dismissed match tracking**: Uses `dismissedMatchRef` to prevent in-flight polls from restoring dismissed matches\n- **Error parsing**: `parseTransactionError()` translates Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages\n- **Balance refresh**: After each tx, refreshes wallet balance\n- **Blockhash refresh**: Re-fetches latest blockhash right before sending to prevent expiry during wallet signing\n\n**Core Actions**:\n1. **`createMatch()`** - Pre-checks for existing match, builds tx, fetches created match\n2. **`joinMatch(matchId)`** - Validates match exists, joins VRF flow\n3. **`cancelMatch()`** - Cancels unclaimed match\n4. **`timeoutCancel()`** - Force-closes if VRF timed out; handles VRF resolution race condition\n5. **`claimPayout()`** - Settles match and marks as claimed\n6. **`selectMatch(match)`** - Opens a claimable match\n7. **`clearActiveMatch()`** - Returns to lobby, records dismissal\n8. **`refreshMatches()`** - Polls open + claimable matches (lobby only)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Coinflip Types (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ntype CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\"\ntype CoinflipPhase = \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"\n\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string                          // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier                          // Iron/Bronze/Silver/Gold/Platinum/Diamond\n  entryAmount: number                 // In SOL (from TIER_AMOUNTS)\n  \n  player1: string                     // Creator address\n  player1Side: CoinSide              // Creator's coin choice\n  \n  player2: string | null              // Opponent (null = waiting)\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null       // Opposite of player1\n  \n  phase: CoinflipPhase               // Current phase\n  createdAt: number                  // Timestamp in ms\n  lockedAt?: number                  // When entered LOCKED (ms)\n  countdownStartedAt?: number        // Countdown start\n  completedAt?: number               // Settlement time\n  \n  result: CoinSide | null            // \"heads\"/\"tails\" (null until settled)\n  winner: string | null              // Winner address (null until settled)\n  \n  claimed: boolean                   // Payout claimed?\n  payoutAmount: number               // Winner's payout (97% of pool)\n  \n  seedHash: string                   // SHA-256 hash (unused currently)\n  serverSeed?: string                // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string                  // VRF proof data\n  blockHash?: string                 // Solana blockhash\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Program ID Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/.env.devnet`\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\n\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n```\n\n### Fallback Values (in code)\n- **COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID**: Falls back to `CoinflipIDL.address` = `\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"`\n- **PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID**: Falls back to `\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"`\n- **ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID**: Hardcoded = `\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"`\n\n### Treasury Constants\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts`\n\n```typescript\nFEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,           // 3%\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200, // 2%\n  RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS: 70,    // 0.7%\n  CHEST_TREASURY_BPS: 30,   // 0.3%\n}\n\nLIMITS = {\n  MAX_FEE_BPS: 1000,\n  MAX_BET_LAMPORTS: 1_000_000_000_000n, // 1000 SOL\n  MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND: 10_000,\n}\n\n// Placeholder program IDs (not actively used in coinflip yet)\nPROGRAM_IDS = {\n  POOL_MANAGER: \"11111111...\",\n  VRF_CONSUMER: \"11111111...\",\n  GAME_CONFIG: \"11111111...\",\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Wallet Provider Architecture\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx`\n\n**Provider Selection Logic**:\n```typescript\nfunction isMockMode(): boolean {\n  const flag = import.meta.env?.VITE_MOCK_MODE;\n  return flag === \"true\";  // Default: false (real wallet)\n}\n\n// In WalletProvider:\nconst inner = isMockMode() \n  ? <MockWalletProvider>{children}</MockWalletProvider>\n  : <Suspense fallback={null}>\n      <RealWalletProvider>{children}</RealWalletProvider>\n    </Suspense>\n```\n\n**Mock vs Real**:\n| Feature | Mock | Real |\n|---------|------|------|\n| Wallet Source | In-memory keypair | Browser extension (Unified Wallet) |\n| RPC | Use VITE_RPC_URL | Use VITE_RPC_URL |\n| Transaction Signing | Client-side | User confirms in extension |\n| State Persistence | LocalStorage (optional) | Extension-managed |\n| Test Mode | Default for CI/tests | Default for production |\n| Failure Simulation | 5% random failure | Real network errors |\n\n**Real Wallet Provider** (`RealWalletProvider.tsx`):\n- Wraps `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` (Unified Wallet Modal)\n- Uses `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` hooks\n- Auto-detects cluster from `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK`\n- Supports dark theme\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Hooks and Integration\n\n**From `@rng-utopia/wallet`**:\n- `useWallet()` - Returns `{ connected, publicKey, sendTransaction, etc. }`\n- `useConnection()` - Returns Solana `Connection` object\n- `useBalance()` - Returns `{ balance, refresh(), ... }`\n\n**Coinflip Integration**:\n```typescript\nconst { connected, publicKey, sendTransaction } = useWallet();\nconst { connection } = useConnection();\nconst { refresh: refreshBalance } = useBalance();\n\n// Sends tx with auto-refresh of blockhash + balance\nconst signature = await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. VRF Resolution Flow\n\n1. **Join Match**: Builds Orao VRF request by deriving `randomnessAccount` from match PDA\n2. **Polling**: Every 5s, checks if Orao fulfilled VRF by reading randomness account (8-byte discriminator + 64 bytes randomness data)\n3. **VRF Callback**: Orao writes randomness; context detects `phase: \"locked\"` → `isVrfFulfilled() == true`\n4. **UI Animation**: Intercepts ready→complete to show flip animation\n5. **Settlement**: `claimPayout()` reads VRF randomness, derives winner on-chain, CPIs to Platform program to update profiles\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Component | Location | Purpose |\n|-----------|----------|---------|\n| TestWalletProvider | `packages/wallet/src/test/` | E2E testing with real keypair |\n| Chain builders | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` | On-chain transaction construction |\n| CoinflipContext | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/` | Game state + polling logic |\n| Types | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` | UI and game data shapes |\n| Treasury | `packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts` | Fee & program constants |\n| WalletProvider | `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` | Mock/Real selection logic |\n| Vite Config | `apps/platform/vite.config.ts` | Build config + polyfills |\n| Env Config | `apps/platform/.env.devnet` | Program IDs + RPC |\n\nAll transaction builders respect Anchor's `accountsStrict()` to prevent account ordering bugs. The context intelligently polls based on phase (5s for VRF pending, 30s for lobby)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac02a6966f001e511 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63782\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 98598</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6036e3a-bc98-4f9f-8839-caeed7dcba03","uuid":"006d41fb-ecdd-4d7c-9686-34b0c569f9de","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the TestWalletProvider and chain integration code in /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/. I need to understand:\n\n1. The TestWalletProvider from packages/wallet/src/ - find the file and read it\n2. The chain.ts transaction builders at apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts\n3. The CoinflipContext.tsx at apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx\n4. The coinflip types at apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts\n5. The anchor program IDs and how they're configured (look for program IDs, env vars, constants)\n\nSearch thoroughly and provide file contents.","agentId":"ac02a6966f001e511","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Comprehensive Code Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the TestWalletProvider and chain integration code in the RNG Utopia codebase. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. TestWalletProvider (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx`)\n\n**Purpose**: E2E testing wallet that signs real transactions with an injected Keypair against local test-validator.\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Uses real Solana keypair signing (no browser extension needed)\n- Default RPC: `http://127.0.0.1:8899` (localhost)\n- Auto-connects on mount by default\n- Implements full `WalletContextValue` interface\n- `sendAndConfirmTransaction()` for real on-chain interaction\n\n**Constructor Props**:\n```typescript\n{\n  keypair: Keypair                    // Real keypair for signing\n  rpcUrl?: string                     // Default: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\n  autoConnect?: boolean               // Default: true\n}\n```\n\n**Methods**:\n- `connect()` - Verifies keypair by checking account balance\n- `disconnect()` - Clears connection state\n- `sendTransaction(tx)` - Signs and confirms transaction with keypair\n- `signMessage(msg)` - Returns deterministic 64-byte signature from keypair's secret key\n\n---\n\n## 2. Chain Transaction Builders (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n\n**Program ID Configuration**:\n```typescript\n// COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID - reads from env or falls back to IDL\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n// IDL address: \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\n\n// ORAO VRF program (hardcoded)\nconst ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\");\n\n// PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID (for CPI to player_profile)\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n);\n```\n\n**PDA Derivation Functions**:\n- `getMatchPda(creator)` - Derives match account PDA from creator\n- `getConfigPda()` - Derives coinflip config PDA\n- `getOraoNetworkStatePda()` - Derives Orao VRF network state\n- `getOraoRandomnessPda(seed)` - Derives Orao randomness request account\n\n**On-Chain Account Types**:\n- `OnChainMatch` interface defines the match struct with fields like phase (enum variant), tier, result, etc.\n- `RoundPhaseVariant` type: `{ waiting | active | locked | resolving | settled | refunded }`\n\n**Converter Functions**:\n- `tierFromIndex()` - Maps index 0-5 to \"iron\", \"bronze\", \"silver\", \"gold\", \"platinum\", \"diamond\"\n- `sideFromIndex()` - Maps 0→\"heads\", 1→\"tails\"\n- `phaseToUI()` - Converts on-chain phase enum to UI phase (\"created\", \"ready\", \"complete\")\n- `onChainMatchToUI()` - Transforms on-chain match account to `UIMatch` type\n\n**Transaction Builders** (all async):\n1. **`buildCreateMatchTx(connection, creator, tier, side)`**\n   - Creates new match with creator and tier\n   - Derives matchPda and configPda\n   - Returns tx + matchPda\n\n2. **`buildJoinMatchTx(connection, opponent, matchCreator)`**\n   - Joins existing match\n   - Fetches Orao treasury from network state\n   - Derives randomness PDA for VRF request\n   - Accounts: opponent, match, config, Orao accounts, system\n\n3. **`buildCancelMatchTx(connection, creator)`**\n   - Cancels unclaimed match (refunds creator)\n   - Only callable before opponent joins\n\n4. **`buildTimeoutCancelTx(connection, caller, matchCreator, opponent)`**\n   - Force-closes locked match if VRF didn't resolve in time\n   - Any player can call after deadline\n\n5. **`buildClaimPayoutTx(connection, caller, matchCreator, opponent)`**\n   - Settlement instruction: resolves VRF randomness, derives winner, sends payout\n   - CPIs to Platform program to update player profiles\n   - Derives both players' profile PDAs\n\n**Query Functions**:\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()` - Filters for \"waiting\" phase matches\n- `fetchClaimableMatches(pubkey)` - Uses memcmp filters for efficient on-chain filtering by creator/opponent + claimed==false\n- `fetchMatchByCreator(creator)` - Fetches single match by creator\n- `fetchMatch(matchPda)` - Fetches match by address\n- All query functions detect VRF fulfillment and upgrade phase \"locked\" → \"complete\" when randomness arrives\n\n---\n\n## 3. CoinflipContext (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\n**State**:\n```typescript\nactiveMatch: UIMatch | null              // Currently-viewing match\nopenMatches: UIMatch[]                  // All available matches from lobby\nclaimableMatches: UIMatch[]            // Matches user is in (as creator or opponent)\nselectedTier: Tier | null              // Selection for new match\nselectedSide: CoinSide | null          // Selection for new match\nloading: boolean                       // Initial load state\ncreating: boolean                      // Create tx in-flight\njoining: boolean                       // Join tx in-flight\nclaiming: boolean                      // Claim payout tx in-flight\njoiningMatchId: string | null          // Which match user is joining\nerror: string | null                   // Last error message\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- **Smart polling**: 5s interval when VRF pending (\"ready\" phase), 30s when in lobby\n- **VRF animation**: Intercepts ready→complete transition to show 3s flip animation before settling\n- **Dismissed match tracking**: Uses `dismissedMatchRef` to prevent in-flight polls from restoring dismissed matches\n- **Error parsing**: `parseTransactionError()` translates Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages\n- **Balance refresh**: After each tx, refreshes wallet balance\n- **Blockhash refresh**: Re-fetches latest blockhash right before sending to prevent expiry during wallet signing\n\n**Core Actions**:\n1. **`createMatch()`** - Pre-checks for existing match, builds tx, fetches created match\n2. **`joinMatch(matchId)`** - Validates match exists, joins VRF flow\n3. **`cancelMatch()`** - Cancels unclaimed match\n4. **`timeoutCancel()`** - Force-closes if VRF timed out; handles VRF resolution race condition\n5. **`claimPayout()`** - Settles match and marks as claimed\n6. **`selectMatch(match)`** - Opens a claimable match\n7. **`clearActiveMatch()`** - Returns to lobby, records dismissal\n8. **`refreshMatches()`** - Polls open + claimable matches (lobby only)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Coinflip Types (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ntype CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\"\ntype CoinflipPhase = \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"countdown\" | \"flipping\" | \"complete\"\n\ninterface UIMatch {\n  id: string                          // Match PDA address (base58)\n  tier: Tier                          // Iron/Bronze/Silver/Gold/Platinum/Diamond\n  entryAmount: number                 // In SOL (from TIER_AMOUNTS)\n  \n  player1: string                     // Creator address\n  player1Side: CoinSide              // Creator's coin choice\n  \n  player2: string | null              // Opponent (null = waiting)\n  player2Side: CoinSide | null       // Opposite of player1\n  \n  phase: CoinflipPhase               // Current phase\n  createdAt: number                  // Timestamp in ms\n  lockedAt?: number                  // When entered LOCKED (ms)\n  countdownStartedAt?: number        // Countdown start\n  completedAt?: number               // Settlement time\n  \n  result: CoinSide | null            // \"heads\"/\"tails\" (null until settled)\n  winner: string | null              // Winner address (null until settled)\n  \n  claimed: boolean                   // Payout claimed?\n  payoutAmount: number               // Winner's payout (97% of pool)\n  \n  seedHash: string                   // SHA-256 hash (unused currently)\n  serverSeed?: string                // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string                  // VRF proof data\n  blockHash?: string                 // Solana blockhash\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Program ID Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/.env.devnet`\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\n\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n```\n\n### Fallback Values (in code)\n- **COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID**: Falls back to `CoinflipIDL.address` = `\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"`\n- **PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID**: Falls back to `\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"`\n- **ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID**: Hardcoded = `\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"`\n\n### Treasury Constants\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts`\n\n```typescript\nFEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,           // 3%\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200, // 2%\n  RAKEBACK_POOL_BPS: 70,    // 0.7%\n  CHEST_TREASURY_BPS: 30,   // 0.3%\n}\n\nLIMITS = {\n  MAX_FEE_BPS: 1000,\n  MAX_BET_LAMPORTS: 1_000_000_000_000n, // 1000 SOL\n  MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND: 10_000,\n}\n\n// Placeholder program IDs (not actively used in coinflip yet)\nPROGRAM_IDS = {\n  POOL_MANAGER: \"11111111...\",\n  VRF_CONSUMER: \"11111111...\",\n  GAME_CONFIG: \"11111111...\",\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Wallet Provider Architecture\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx`\n\n**Provider Selection Logic**:\n```typescript\nfunction isMockMode(): boolean {\n  const flag = import.meta.env?.VITE_MOCK_MODE;\n  return flag === \"true\";  // Default: false (real wallet)\n}\n\n// In WalletProvider:\nconst inner = isMockMode() \n  ? <MockWalletProvider>{children}</MockWalletProvider>\n  : <Suspense fallback={null}>\n      <RealWalletProvider>{children}</RealWalletProvider>\n    </Suspense>\n```\n\n**Mock vs Real**:\n| Feature | Mock | Real |\n|---------|------|------|\n| Wallet Source | In-memory keypair | Browser extension (Unified Wallet) |\n| RPC | Use VITE_RPC_URL | Use VITE_RPC_URL |\n| Transaction Signing | Client-side | User confirms in extension |\n| State Persistence | LocalStorage (optional) | Extension-managed |\n| Test Mode | Default for CI/tests | Default for production |\n| Failure Simulation | 5% random failure | Real network errors |\n\n**Real Wallet Provider** (`RealWalletProvider.tsx`):\n- Wraps `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` (Unified Wallet Modal)\n- Uses `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` hooks\n- Auto-detects cluster from `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK`\n- Supports dark theme\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Hooks and Integration\n\n**From `@rng-utopia/wallet`**:\n- `useWallet()` - Returns `{ connected, publicKey, sendTransaction, etc. }`\n- `useConnection()` - Returns Solana `Connection` object\n- `useBalance()` - Returns `{ balance, refresh(), ... }`\n\n**Coinflip Integration**:\n```typescript\nconst { connected, publicKey, sendTransaction } = useWallet();\nconst { connection } = useConnection();\nconst { refresh: refreshBalance } = useBalance();\n\n// Sends tx with auto-refresh of blockhash + balance\nconst signature = await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. VRF Resolution Flow\n\n1. **Join Match**: Builds Orao VRF request by deriving `randomnessAccount` from match PDA\n2. **Polling**: Every 5s, checks if Orao fulfilled VRF by reading randomness account (8-byte discriminator + 64 bytes randomness data)\n3. **VRF Callback**: Orao writes randomness; context detects `phase: \"locked\"` → `isVrfFulfilled() == true`\n4. **UI Animation**: Intercepts ready→complete to show flip animation\n5. **Settlement**: `claimPayout()` reads VRF randomness, derives winner on-chain, CPIs to Platform program to update profiles\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Component | Location | Purpose |\n|-----------|----------|---------|\n| TestWalletProvider | `packages/wallet/src/test/` | E2E testing with real keypair |\n| Chain builders | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` | On-chain transaction construction |\n| CoinflipContext | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/` | Game state + polling logic |\n| Types | `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` | UI and game data shapes |\n| Treasury | `packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts` | Fee & program constants |\n| WalletProvider | `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` | Mock/Real selection logic |\n| Vite Config | `apps/platform/vite.config.ts` | Build config + polyfills |\n| Env Config | `apps/platform/.env.devnet` | Program IDs + RPC |\n\nAll transaction builders respect Anchor's `accountsStrict()` to prevent account ordering bugs. The context intelligently polls based on phase (5s for VRF pending, 30s for lobby)."}],"totalDurationMs":98598,"totalTokens":63782,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1053,"cache_read_input_tokens":58645,"output_tokens":4078,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1053,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
