{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013PL1SqX8rXzdds9KLyBnA7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the info I need. The first unchecked item is:\n\n```\n- [ ] [test] Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`) separated from visual and real-wallet smoke tests\n```\n\nI need to:\n\n1. Create `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — a new Playwright config for local E2E tests\n2. Create `apps/platform/e2e/local/` directory with at least one placeholder spec\n3. The config should:\n   - Use `VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"` (real wallet mode, not mock)\n   - Use `VITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"` (local validator)\n   - Have testMatch pointing to `local/**/*.spec.ts`\n   - Use a different port (e.g., 3002) to avoid conflicts\n   - Not include visual regression snapshot settings\n4. Add the `test:e2e` script to both the platform and root package.json files\n\nLooking back at the spec, I see the distinction now — there's a separate checklist item for wiring up the command itself. For this particular item, I need to focus on the config and directory structure: create `playwright.local.config.ts`, set up the `e2e/local/` directory with an initial test, and make sure the local configuration is properly isolated from the visual and devnet suites.\n\nThe key is that this local config needs its own environment setup — running against a local test validator on port 3002 with real wallet mode enabled and the RPC pointing to `http://127.0.0.1:8899`.\n\nNow I'm setting up the test file pattern to match files in the `e2e/local/` directory, and since these are functional tests rather than visual ones, I don't need screenshot or snapshot configurations. I'll also add a script to the platform package.json to run these tests with the local config.\n\nFor the Playwright configuration itself, I need to decide on the environment setup: port 3002 to avoid conflicts, mock mode disabled so we use the real TestWalletProvider, and point to a local test validator at `http://127.0.0.1:8899`. The webServer should start Vite since the bootstrap script will handle the broader setup later. Let me create the config file and add a basic smoke test to verify everything's wired correctly. I'm thinking through what files to create for this checklist item - I need the Playwright config for local E2E testing, the directory structure, and a script to run it. Let me set up the config file, create the e2e/local directory with a placeholder, and add the test:e2e:local script to package.json.\n\nNow I'm realizing the default playwright.config.ts runs everything in the e2e/ directory without filtering, so if I add e2e/local/, it would pick those up too. I should update the default config to use testMatch or testIgnore so it only runs visual tests and doesn't accidentally include the local tests.\n\nMy plan is to update the default config to match only visual tests, create a separate local config file, set up the local test directory with a placeholder, and add the corresponding npm script.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7725,"cache_read_input_tokens":49112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7725},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6036e3a-bc98-4f9f-8839-caeed7dcba03","uuid":"7b283542-0528-4a1f-8ea0-a1957773c364"}
